OL,3,CChina clay mining explained as
OL,4,Cmillions invested in Cornwall
OL,6,FWhat is china clay and how is it mined?
OL,8,FChina clay is a material known as
OL,9,Fkaolin, which was first used in China
OL,10,Fmore than 10 thousand years ago to
OL,11,Fmake fine white porcelain. Some of
OL,12,Fthis eventually made its way to Europe.
OL,14,FNoticing a gap in the market, a
OL,15,FPlymouth apothecary began to research
OL,16,Fthe porcelain-making process and spent
OL,17,Fseveral years searching for a material
OL,18,Fthat resembled kaolin. In 1745 he
OL,19,Ffound it, at Tregonning Hill in
OL,20,FCornwall.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/8
