OL,3,CChina clay mining explained as
OL,4,Cmillions invested in Cornwall
OL,6,FBy the mid 19th century 65,000 tonnes
OL,7,Fof china clay were being mined from
OL,8,Fthe St Austell area every year by
OL,9,F7,000 workers.
OL,11,FKaolin is traditionally extracted from
OL,12,Fmines using a hydraulic mining method.
OL,13,FThis is a wet process where high
OL,14,Fpressure water washes the clay from
OL,15,Fthe granite - forming a slurry to
OL,16,Ftransport it via pipes to a drying
OL,17,Fsite.
OL,19,FA new dry mining technique will be
OL,20,Fused at Imerys' new site, which
OL,21,Fexpends less water and electricity.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/8
